---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Editorial Policy', path: '/editorial-policy/' }]}>
  <div class="page-shell py-4 sm:py-5">
    <div class="page-main">
      <p class="folio mb-4">Editorial Policy</p>
      <div class="prose-nlu">
      <h2>Source material</h2>
      <p>
        Essays and framework pages are derived from published or forthcoming academic research, primarily
        SSRN working papers by Liang Zhang. They are not substitutes for the full papers.
      </p>
      <h2>One paper, many essays</h2>
      <p>
        A single research paper may be translated into multiple essays placed in different columns when
        the same argument speaks to different professional audiences — for example, a latency paper may
        yield both a society essay on justice and a life essay on everyday waiting.
      </p>
      <h2>Citation</h2>
      <p>
        For academic citation, use the original SSRN paper. For general reference to an essay on this
        site, cite the essay URL and date published.
      </p>
      <h2>Editorial standards</h2>
      <p>
        Essay voice, structure, and publication checklist are maintained in the repository document
        <code>docs/EDITORIAL-BIBLE.md</code> (Editorial Bible). Essays are adapted from named sections of
        source papers; each essay page includes a formal source attribution in the footer.
      </p>
      <h2>Editor's Notes</h2>
      <p>
        Editor's Notes are editorial commentary on the research program. They may precede or synthesize
        formal papers and are clearly labeled as editor's writing.
      </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
